article.description: Kahlil Felder scored 28 points with seven assists and Oakland had six players in double figures, racing to a 111-93 win over Green Bay on Saturday.
article.headline: Felder's 28 leads Oakland to 111-93 win over Green Bay
article.linkText: Felder's 28 leads Oakland to 111-93 win over Green Bay
article.story: ROCHESTER, Mich. -- Kahlil Felder scored 28 points with seven assists and Oakland had six players in double figures, racing to a 111-93 win over Green Bay on Saturday. Nick Daniels added 17 points and six assists and three players had 12 as the Golden Grizzlies (18-9, 10-4 Horizon League) hit 111 for the second time this season. They beat the Phoenix 111-95 on Jan. 23. Oakland beat Missouri-Kansas City 114-105 in overtime on Dec. 6, 2007. Oakland led 52-42 at the half and then shot better than 60 percent, pushing the lead to 35 with 7:13 to play, until cooling off down the stretch. The Golden Grizzlies finished at 51 percent (35 of 69), including 12 for 30 on 3-pointers and 29 of 33 from the foul line. Charles Cooper and Tevin Findlay had 18 apiece for the Phoenix (15-11, 7-6).
